{"lemma":"بَرَكَةُ","slug":"بَرَكَةُ","root":"ب.ر.ك","root_slug":"ب-ر-ك","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ر-ك","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"بَرَكَة","root":"برك","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2362","n2363","n2364","n2365"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%83%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bliss, blessing, boon"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pond"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pool"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tank"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"receptacle"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mode of kneeling (بُرُوك (burūk))"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"an unknown kind of small white aquatic bird","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mallard"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Hebrew בריכה (brekhá, “pond, pool”)."},"ipa":["/ba.ra.ka/","/bir.ka/","/bur.ka/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2362","headword_ar":"بُرْكَةٌ","root":"brk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burakapN","text_ar":"بُرَكَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain aquatic bird, white,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and small:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) [the former applied in Barbary, in the present day, to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a duck:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burakN","text_ar":"بُرَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burokaAnN","text_ar":"بُرْكَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"birokaAnN","text_ar":"بِرْكَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [pl. of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboraAkN","text_ar":"اَبْرَاكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) or, in the opinion of ISd,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AbrAk","text_ar":"ابراك"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"brkAn","text_ar":"بركان"},{"kind":"text","text":"are pls. of the pl. ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burakN","text_ar":"بُرَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n2363","headword_ar":"بِرْكَةٌ","root":"brk","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwk","text_ar":"بُرُوك"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. of a camel's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kneeling and lying down upon the breast"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, * O, * K;) a noun like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rikobapN","text_ar":"رِكْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jilosapN","text_ar":"جِلْسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^aHosana birokapa h`*ihi Aln~aAqapi","text_ar":"مَا اَحْسَنَ بِرْكَةَ هٰذِهِ النَّاقَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How good is this she-camel's manner of lying down on the breast!"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barokN","text_ar":"بَرْكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawoD","text_ar":"حَوْض"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"watering-trough"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tank"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dug in the ground, not having raised sides constructed for it above the surface of the ground;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"birokN","text_ar":"بِرْكٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: (Lth, K:) said to be so called because of the continuance of the water therein: (S:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"birakN","text_ar":"بِرَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) which Az found to be applied by the Arabs to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tanks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cisterns, that are constructed with baked bricks, and plastered with lime, in the road to Mekkeh, and at its wateringplaces;"},{"kind":"text","text":"sing."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"birokapN","text_ar":"بِرْكَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and sometimes a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"brkp","text_ar":"بركة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a thousand cubits [in length], and less, and more: but the watering-troughs, or tanks, that are made for the rain-water, and not cased with baked bricks, are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSonaAEN","text_ar":"اَصْنَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", sing."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SinoEN","text_ar":"صِنْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"birokapN","text_ar":"بِرْكَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"often signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a basin; a pool; a pond;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lake:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in the present day, also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bay of the sea:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a reach of a river:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place where water remains and collects,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"collects and stagnates,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remains long and becomes altered."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, K.)"}],"source_refs":["K","S","TA","Lth","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n2364","headword_ar":"بَرَكَةٌ","root":"brk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A blessing; any good that is bestowed by God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as continues and increases and abounds:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel in xi. 50,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or prosperity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good fortune,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that proceeds from God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, in explanation of the pl. as used in the Kur xi. 76:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"increase; accession; redundance; abundance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plenty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, Kull;) whether"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sensible"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intellectual:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"continuance of divinely-bestowed good, such as is perceived by the intellect, in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon, a thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kull:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"firmness, stability,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"continuance, coupled with increase:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 587:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"increasing good:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in xi. 50:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundance of good; implying the meaning of increase, accession,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"redundance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in xxv. 1:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundant and continual good:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(so in an Expos. of the Jámi' es-Sagheer, cited in the margin of a copy of the MS:) and, accord. to Az, God's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"superiority over everything."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Fr","K","Kull"]},{"entry_id":"n2365","headword_ar":"بُرَكَةٌ","root":"brk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burokapN","text_ar":"بُرْكَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}